ss should still be counted. I need a better approach, focusing on JVM agent coverage. The dynamic report might come from the javaTest run, but earlier results show JCEDHPublicKey tests passed. Yet, if the coverage report is built from the native run, it may exclude any failures. Time to inspect those timestamps!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring serialization behavior**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether dynamic-access instrumentation only treats call sites when the caller class, JCEDHPublicKey, is loaded from the library jar, particularly in the context of a native image. Our serialized stream was originally created using reflection, and deserialization should invoke `JCEDHPublicKey.readObject`. The test uses a constant serialized stream, which includes fields like dhSpec, info, and y. However, for a class with a private `writeObject` and no `defaultWriteObject`, `ObjectInputStream` creates the object without setting any fields before calling the private `readObject`. Is it possible that `JCEDHPublicKey` doesn't implement `Serializable`?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3e8OdegYgnt23d4r1j4lCFwy|fc_0f7747aecb615386016a10dac6c66c81929946138911c0bc81", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/JCEDHPublicKeyTest.java", "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 34763, "output": 575, "cacheRead": 50688, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 86026, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779489456006, "responseId": "resp_0f7747aecb615386016a10dab1b6e08192acb19acb0009764b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_3e8OdegYgnt23d4r1j4lCFwy|fc_0f7747aecb615386016a10dac6c66c81929946138911c0bc81", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectStreamClass;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.math.BigInteger;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Base64;\n\nimport javax.crypto.interfaces.DHPublicKey;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.JCEDHPublicKey;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class JCEDHPublicKeyTest {\n    private static final BigInteger P = BigInteger.valueOf(23L);\n    private static final BigInteger G = BigInteger.valueOf(5L);\n    private static final BigInteger Y = BigInteger.valueOf(8L);\n\n    @Test\n    void serializedJcePublicKeyRoundTripPreservesDhParameters() throws Exception {\n        JCEDHPublicKey publicKey = (JCEDHPublicKey) deserialize(serializedJcePublicKey());\n\n        JCEDHPublicKey restoredKey = (JCEDHPublicKey) deserialize(serialize(publicKey));\n\n        assertJcePublicKey(restoredKey);\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getEncoded()).isEqualTo(publicKey.getEncoded());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void serializedHolderRoundTripPreservesNestedJcePublicKey() throws Exception {\n        JCEDHPublicKey publicKey = (JCEDHPublicKey) deserialize(serializedJcePublicKey());\n        KeyHolder holder = new KeyHolder(publicKey);\n\n        KeyHolder restoredHolder = (KeyHolder) deserialize(serialize(holder));\n\n        assertThat(restoredHolder.publicKey).isInstanceOf(JCEDHPublicKey.class);\n        assertJcePublicKey(restoredHolder.publicKey);\n    }\n\n    private static void assertJcePublicKey(DHPublicKey publicKey) {\n        assertThat(publicKey.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"DH\");\n        assertThat(publicKey.getFormat()).isEqualTo(\"X.509\");\n        assertThat(publicKey.getY()).isEqualTo(Y);\n        assertThat(publicKey.getParams().getP()).isEqualTo(P);\n        assertThat(publicKey.getParams().getG()).isEqualTo(G);\n        assertThat(publicKey.getParams().getL()).isZero();\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serializedJcePublicKey() {\n        byte[] serializedKey = Base64.getMimeDecoder().decode(\"\"\"\n                rO0ABXNyACxvcmcuYm91bmN5Y2FzdGxlLmpjZS5wcm92aWRlci5KQ0VESFB1YmxpY0tlefz+KCkPI+T8\n                AwADTAAGZGhTcGVjdAAjTGphdmF4L2NyeXB0by9zcGVjL0RIUGFyYW1ldGVyU3BlYztMAARpbmZvdAAx\n                TG9yZy9ib3VuY3ljYXN0bGUvYXNuMS94NTA5L1N1YmplY3RQdWJsaWNLZXlJbmZvO0wAAXl0ABZMamF2\n                YS9tYXRoL0JpZ0ludGVnZXI7eHBzcgAUamF2YS5tYXRoLkJpZ0ludGVnZXKM/J8fqTv7HQMABkkACGJp\n                dENvdW50SQAJYml0TGVuZ3RoSQATZmlyc3ROb256ZXJvQnl0ZU51bUkADGxvd2VzdFNldEJpdEkABnNp\n                Z251bVsACW1hZ25pdHVkZXQAAltCeHIAEGphdmEubGFuZy5OdW1iZXKGrJUdC5TgiwIAAHhw////////\n                ///////+/////gAAAAF1cgACW0Ks8xf4BghU4AIAAHhwAAAAAQh4c3EAfgAF///////////////+////\n                /gAAAAF1cQB+AAkAAAABF3hzcQB+AAX///////////////7////+AAAAAXVxAH4ACQAAAAEFeHcEAAAA\n                AHg=\n                \"\"\");\n        patchSerialVersionUid(serializedKey, JCEDHPublicKey.class);\n        return serializedKey;\n    }\n\n    private static void patchSerialVersionUid(byte[] serializedValue, Class<?> serializedClass) {\n        byte[] className = serializedClass.getName().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        int uidOffset = indexOf(serializedValue, className) + className.length;\n        if (uidOffset < className.length) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\"Serialized class descriptor not found for \" + serializedClass.getName());\n        }\n\n        long serialVersionUid = ObjectStreamClass.lookup(serializedClass).getSerialVersionUID();\n        for (int index = Long.BYTES - 1; index >= 0; index--) {\n            serializedValue[uidOffset + index] = (byte) serialVersionUid;\n            serialVersionUid >>>= Byte.SIZE;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static int indexOf(byte[] source, byte[] target) {\n        for (int sourceIndex = 0; sourceIndex <= source.length - target.length; sourceIndex++) {\n            boolean found = true;\n            for (int targetIndex = 0; targetIndex < target.length; targetIndex++) {\n                if (source[sourceIndex + targetIndex] != target[targetIndex]) {\n                    found = false;\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n            if (found) {\n                return sourceIndex;\n            }\n        }\n        return -1;\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(Object value) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectStream = new ObjectOutputStream(byteStream)) {\n            objectStream.writeObject(value);\n        }\n        return byteStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static Object deserialize(byte[] serializedValue) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedValue))) {\n            return objectStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class KeyHolder implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private final DHPublicKey publicKey;\n\n        private KeyHolder(DHPublicKey publicKey) {\n            this.publicKey = publicKey;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779489479159}]}
